<section class="ced-incubation-alt">

  <div class="container">

    <!-- HEADER -->
    <div class="header-block">
      <h1>CED Pre-Incubation (CEDi)</h1>
      <div class="header-line"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- INTRO -->
    <div class="intro-box fade-in">
      <p>
        <strong>CED’s Pre-Incubation</strong> (often referred to as “<strong>CEDi</strong>” /
        Pre-incubator) is a structured support pathway designed to take early-stage
        student ideas and help them mature into viable startup ventures before they
        enter formal incubation. It’s not just an orientation — it’s hands-on support
        with measurable outcomes:
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- CORE COMPONENTS -->
    <h2 class="section-title">⚙️ Core Components</h2>

    <div class="row g-4">

      <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="feature-card slide-up">
          <h3>1. Mentoring & Guided Coaching</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>1-on-1 expert mentoring to refine problem statements, business models and go-to-market strategy.</li>
            <li>Focus on converting raw ideas into prototype-ready solutions.</li>
            <li>Guidance on application of Design Thinking, strategic planning and business validation.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="feature-card slide-up delay-1">
          <h3>2. Prototyping Support through MAKERS LAB</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Access to tools and equipment for rapid prototype development (3D printing, PCB design tools, embedded systems, IoT devices, etc.).</li>
            <li>CED’s Makers Lab is part of the pre-incubation ecosystem — not a separate group.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="feature-card slide-up delay-2">
          <h3>3. Business & Legal Support</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Assistance with company registration steps, intellectual property (IP) advice, legal basics, funding readiness.</li>
            <li>Help with applying for government-linked grants (e.g., Innovation Voucher Program) once pre-incubated.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="feature-card slide-up delay-3">
          <h3>4. Access to Network & Funding Pathways</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Introductions to investors, industry mentors and ecosystem partners.</li>
            <li>Connection with events like Startup Café and Startify where pre-incubated ideas can get visibility and early funding opportunities.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>







  <!-- ================= GRANTS / FUNDING SECTION ================= -->
<h2 class="section-title">💰 Startups that Received Grants / Funding</h2>

<div class="grants-box fade-in">
  <p>
    Several startups nurtured through <strong>CED Pre-Incubation</strong> have
    successfully secured <strong>grants and funding support</strong> from
    government and ecosystem programs.
  </p>

  <a
    href="https://www.auced.com/grants_received"
    target="_blank"
    class="grants-link"
  >
    🔗 View List of Startups that Received Grants / Funding
  </a>
</div>








    <!-- PROCESS -->
    <h2 class="section-title mt-5">🧪 What Happens During Pre-Incubation</h2>

    <p class="process-intro">
      The process — again, not hype — typically looks like this:
    </p>

    <div class="timeline">

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <span class="dot"></span>
        <div>
          <strong>Idea Screening & Shortlisting</strong>
          <p>
            Ideas from students (and sometimes faculty) are reviewed. Viability is evaluated
            based on innovation potential & basic market sense.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <span class="dot"></span>
        <div>
          <strong>Bootcamps & Workshops</strong>
          <p>
            Structured sessions on ideation, market validation, business modelling and
            prototyping skills.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <span class="dot"></span>
        <div>
          <strong>Prototype Build & Review</strong>
          <p>
            Iterative development with feedback loops; prototypes are built in Makers Lab.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <span class="dot"></span>
        <div>
          <strong>Pitching & External Exposure</strong>
          <p>
            Teams pitch to panels of mentors/investors; high-performers may get support to
            get seed funding or move toward full incubation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- STATEMENT -->
    <div class="center-highlight fade-in">
      “CED Pre-Incubator” helping nurture student innovations into early business ventures.
    </div>

    <!-- NOTE -->
    <div class="final-note fade-in">
      This is not an incubator in the sense of providing long-term residency or large
      funding — it’s specifically a pre-incubation funnel:
      <strong>
        idea → prototype → early validation → pathway to seed or formal incubation.
      </strong>
    </div>












